  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The COU narrative further specifies that the model must remain valid only for impeller tip speeds strictly below 6.0 m/s, as exceedance of this threshold has been linked to clinically significant erythrocyte membrane disruption in the CPB literature; accordingly, all simulation operating points were constrained to tip speeds not exceeding 5.8 m/s. This tip-speed ceiling is treated as a binding safety property of the credibility claim.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
